<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="ashamed-adj">ashamed <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'ʃeɪmd/    美 /ə'ʃeɪmd/  </p>
<p>[不用于名词前]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-proud">1.★ <strong>羞耻的；惭愧的【反：proud 】；害臊的：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) ashamed of sb / sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You should be ashamed of your foolish behavior. 
你应对自己的愚蠢行为感到羞耻。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was <strong>ashamed of myself</strong>.
我为自己感到惭愧。</p><footer>2016 浙江</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) ashamed to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m ashamed to admit that I’ve never read Harry Potter.
我真不好意思承认我从未读过《哈利·波特》。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) ashamed + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was ashamed that he couldn’t give an answer. 
他因回答不出问题而感到羞愧。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Tom was <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (羞愧) of having lied to his parents.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. ashamed  </p></div>